description:
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England is seeking applications for a Corporate Affairs Business Manager. This role will form part of the national Corporate Affairs Team and the successful candidate will be based at their nearest HEE office location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Corporate Affairs Manager will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering an effective Corporate Affairs function supporting managers and staff across the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will manage the office of the Head of Corporate Affairs and take the lead on ensuring the effective management and planning of a range of project work on behalf of the Head of Corporate Affairs, whilst ensuring that the teams programmes of activity and services are planned and managed effectively and take the lead in assisting in their successful delivery. They will play a key role in managing the day to day running of the Head of Corporate Affairs corporate business, including organising meetings and events for a range of senior stakeholders ensuring the preparation of agendas, all logistical arrangements, note/formal minute taking and producing records. The business manager will also be responsible for management of the teams pay and non-pay budget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be expected to lead on discrete projects, carrying out research and development plans as directed and required by senior managers in the Corporate Affairs Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who enjoys working as a member of a team showing a high level of adaptability and a flexible approach to work, and who is committed to quality and continuous improvement. You will need to be a team player, used to working with colleagues at all levels, innovative and solution focused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 7 with a full-time starting salary of £38,890, with pay step increases after 2 years’ service and 5 years’ service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to Covid-19 this role will operate on a working from home basis until further notice, all equipment required will be provided. Travel may be expected, at a time that it is safe to do so.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Simon Baughan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Regional Corporate Affairs Business Parnter&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: simon.baughan@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07795718485&lt;/p&gt;
